OL,7,FReading a statement on behalf of the
OL,8,FArmy, Brigadier Melissa Emmett, the
OL,9,Fhead of the Army Personnel Services
OL,10,FGroup told reporters after the
OL,11,Finquest: "On behalf of the Chief of
OL,12,Fthe General Staff, I wish to extend
OL,13,Fthe Army's deepest condolences to
OL,14,FJaysley's family and friends, and to
OL,15,Foffer them our sincerest apologies for
OL,16,Fthe failings that the coroner has
OL,17,Fidentified during this inquest."
OL,26,@sD@JOUyD@`O]
